D. Removing spaces before column names for data wrangling¶

In [238]:
#To remove the space between the column list_price
# Get the current column names with spaces
current_column_names = KPMGtransactions.columns

# Remove spaces from column names
new_column_names = [name.replace(' ', '') for name in current_column_names]

# Rename the columns with the new names
KPMGtransactions.rename(columns=dict(zip(current_column_names, new_column_names)), inplace=True)

2. Outlier Detection¶

A. KPMGtransactions dataset¶

In [250]:
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Assuming you have loaded your data into a pandas DataFrame called 'df'

def is_numerical(column):
    # Check if the column contains numerical data (integers or floating-point numbers)
    return pd.api.types.is_numeric_dtype(column)

def plot_box_plots(dataframe):
    for column_name in dataframe.columns:
        if is_numerical(dataframe[column_name]):
            plt.figure(figsize=(6, 4))
            plt.boxplot(dataframe[column_name], vert=False)
            plt.title(f'Box Plot for {column_name}')
            plt.xlabel(column_name)
            plt.show()

# Call the function to plot box plots for all numerical columns in the DataFrame
plot_box_plots(KPMGtransactions)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Assuming you have loaded your data into a pandas DataFrame called 'df'

def is_numerical(column):
    # Check if the column contains numerical data (integers or floating-point numbers)
    return pd.api.types.is_numeric_dtype(column)

def plot_box_plots(dataframe):
    for column_name in dataframe.columns:
        if is_numerical(dataframe[column_name]):
            plt.figure(figsize=(6, 4))
            plt.boxplot(dataframe[column_name], vert=False)
            plt.title(f'Box Plot for {column_name}')
            plt.xlabel(column_name)
            plt.show()

# Call the function to plot box plots for all numerical columns in the DataFrame
plot_box_plots(Customer_address)

Additional data processing step¶
We need to convert the followoing:¶
1. F to female¶
2. Femal to female¶
3. M to Male¶
In [270]:
# Create a dictionary for the replacements
gender_mapping = {
    'F': 'Female',
    'Femal': 'Female',
    'M': 'Male'
}

# Apply the mapping to the 'gender' column
Customer_demographic['gender'] = Customer_demographic['gender'].map(gender_mapping)
